MIVIA HEp-2 Image dataset
A dataset of 28 HEp-2 cell images, one per patient, used for cell image segmentation in the lab.

MATLAB
A software company that produces MATLAB, used in this lab for image processing tasks such as grayscale conversion.

Lab Instructor
The instructor who provided the image dataset and binary masks for reference in the lab.

Digital Image Processing Lab Report
A lab report detailing the process of cell image segmentation using digital image processing techniques.

Cell Image Segmentation
The process of identifying and separating individual cells from a digital image.

rgb2gray
A MATLAB function used for grayscale conversion of images.

CLAHE (Contrast Limited Adaptive Histogram Equalization)
An image processing technique used for contrast enhancement.

Otsu's method
A thresholding method that assumes a bimodal histogram distribution.

Adaptive thresholding
A thresholding method that adjusts thresholds based on local intensity.

Morphological opening
A morphological operation used for removing small objects from a binary image.

Morphological closing
A morphological operation used for filling holes in a binary image.

Connected component analysis
An algorithm used to identify and label connected regions in a binary image.

Binary masks
Images that highlight the regions of interest (ROIs) in the cell images.

Regions of Interest (ROI)
Specific areas within an image that are of interest for analysis, in this case, the areas containing cells.

Grayscale Conversion
The process of converting a color image to a grayscale image.

Histogram Analysis
The process of analyzing the distribution of pixel intensities in an image.

Contrast Normalization
The process of adjusting the contrast in an image to improve visibility.

Thresholding
The process of converting a grayscale image to a binary image by setting a threshold value.

Morphological Operations
Image processing techniques that modify the shape and size of objects in an image.

Connected Component Labeling
The process of identifying and labeling connected regions in a binary image.

Visual Inspection
The process of manually inspecting the results of image processing to assess quality.
